00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:39,999
=The Litchi Road=

2
00:01:40,020 --> 00:01:40,820
(Counting Rods and Hoe)

3
00:01:40,840 --> 00:01:43,377
Bureau of Agriculture
supervises grain reserves,

4
00:01:43,430 --> 00:01:44,888
granaries, and all related affairs.

5
00:01:44,911 --> 00:01:47,400
(Ten Years Ago, Archive Hall)
The Archive Hall is a restricted area.

6
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:49,150
All official documents are stored here

7
00:01:49,950 --> 00:01:52,044
for inspection and review at any time.

8
00:01:56,070 --> 00:01:56,910
Remember this.

9
00:01:57,311 --> 00:01:59,333
Whoever comes to view the documents,

10
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:01,088
you must report to me immediately.

11
00:02:01,430 --> 00:02:02,270
Understood, Sir.

12
00:02:04,488 --> 00:02:06,355
You've passed the arithmetic exam

13
00:02:06,377 --> 00:02:07,777
and just started your post.

14
00:02:07,950 --> 00:02:09,710
Don't get ahead of yourself.

15
00:02:10,177 --> 00:02:12,000
Get familiar
with your surroundings first.

16
00:02:12,911 --> 00:02:14,080
As part of your daily routine,

17
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:15,590
be sure to thoroughly dust

18
00:02:16,030 --> 00:02:17,150
the shelves.

19
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:18,840
All scrolls here

20
00:02:19,150 --> 00:02:21,280
must be properly sorted

21
00:02:21,355 --> 00:02:22,777
by prefecture, country, and date.

22
00:02:23,750 --> 00:02:24,750
Be meticulous.

23
00:02:25,750 --> 00:02:27,155
Don't make mistakes.

24
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:30,000
Don't underestimate these documents.

25
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:31,840
Everything here

26
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:33,590
is the very foundation

27
00:02:34,430 --> 00:02:36,244
of the people's livelihood.

28
00:02:36,590 --> 00:02:37,960
I will be cautious

29
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:40,133
and leave no stone unturned.

30
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:45,430
Recorder Meng is strict.

31
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:47,870
Previously, two overseers
were sent to serve

32
00:02:47,870 --> 00:02:48,840
at provincial granaries

33
00:02:49,310 --> 00:02:51,310
for making errors.

34
00:02:53,111 --> 00:02:54,240
How long do you think

35
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:56,155
this one lasts?

36
00:03:05,470 --> 00:03:06,310
Three days.

37
00:03:06,590 --> 00:03:07,430
At most.

38
00:03:13,700 --> 00:03:16,540
(Main Granary, Jingzhao
Administrative Division, Wanji County)

39
00:03:16,540 --> 00:03:20,940
(Recorded a total of 815 dan.
Millet, sorghum, maize, wheat, rice)

40
00:03:32,820 --> 00:03:35,580
(Main Granary, Jingzhao
Administrative Division, Wanji County)

41
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:49,800
Who's there?

42
00:03:49,888 --> 00:03:52,155
This is the Vice Minister
of Bureau of Agriculture.

43
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:54,680
Please pardon me.

44
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:56,311
Greetings, Sir.

45
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:57,360
Who are you?

46
00:03:58,630 --> 00:03:59,470
Where is

47
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:00,920
Recorder Meng?

48
00:04:02,630 --> 00:04:04,533
I guess he hasn't arrived yet.

49
00:04:05,310 --> 00:04:06,630
I'm Li Shande.

50
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:09,430
I joined yesterday.

51
00:04:10,310 --> 00:04:12,870
While sorting scrolls last night,

52
00:04:12,870 --> 00:04:14,333
I found some inconsistencies.

53
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:15,750
I spent the night recalculating

54
00:04:15,870 --> 00:04:17,070
and fell asleep.

55
00:04:17,666 --> 00:04:18,960
You just joined the office

56
00:04:19,733 --> 00:04:21,155
and already found mistakes?

57
00:04:21,510 --> 00:04:22,955
Please have a look, Sir.

58
00:04:25,630 --> 00:04:28,288
This is the storage record
for this year.

59
00:04:31,750 --> 00:04:33,190
This is the release record

60
00:04:33,190 --> 00:04:34,377
from last winter.

61
00:04:36,870 --> 00:04:37,920
And this is the measurement

62
00:04:37,977 --> 00:04:39,488
of the large granary storage container.

63
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:43,840
I figure

64
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:45,870
the reported figures may be inaccurate

65
00:04:45,870 --> 00:04:47,355
or there are some hidden figures.

66
00:04:49,111 --> 00:04:51,910
The storage records are overseen
by both the minister

67
00:04:51,911 --> 00:04:54,800
and the censorate
before being filed.

68
00:04:55,088 --> 00:04:57,160
The release records are handled
by the recorder,

69
00:04:57,390 --> 00:04:58,680
based on source

70
00:04:58,920 --> 00:05:00,000
and type of grain,

71
00:05:00,111 --> 00:05:02,355
and cross-checked
with the wooden calibration wedges

72
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:04,240
of the issuer

73
00:05:04,688 --> 00:05:07,320
and the chief of each granary
before the grain release.

74
00:05:07,466 --> 00:05:09,310
Multiple parties are involved
in the inspection.

75
00:05:09,310 --> 00:05:10,490
How could there be a mistake?

76
00:05:11,270 --> 00:05:12,110
I believe

77
00:05:12,630 --> 00:05:14,955
grain is the foundation of the people

78
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:16,600
as well as our prime duty.

79
00:05:16,977 --> 00:05:18,600
If our records and inventories

80
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:19,720
aren't handled precisely,

81
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:21,310
even the slightest discrepancy

82
00:05:21,310 --> 00:05:23,333
can result in great differences.

83
00:05:23,360 --> 00:05:24,488
Both publicly and privately,

84
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:26,355
this is a grave mistake.

85
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:28,666
You may not be fully aware
of the entire picture.

86
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:30,040
You can't judge based on these...

87
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:31,000
Please read this, Sir.

88
00:05:34,888 --> 00:05:36,630
Twelve large granary
storage containers with,

89
00:05:36,630 --> 00:05:38,460
a top diameter of 3 meters,
bottom of 3 meters,

90
00:05:38,630 --> 00:05:39,630
and height of 4 meters.

91
00:05:39,630 --> 00:05:42,088
Thirteen small granary storage
containers. Top diameter 3 meters...

92
00:05:45,580 --> 00:05:47,020
(Millet, sorghum, maize, wheat, rice)

93
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:48,160
After calculations,

94
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:50,333
the total should be 8,067 dan.

95
00:05:50,390 --> 00:05:53,070
Therefore, the figure in the document

96
00:05:53,160 --> 00:05:54,920
and the actual record

97
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:56,800
differ by 186 dan.

98
00:06:00,866 --> 00:06:02,355
This is indeed an error.

99
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:12,733
May I take these scrolls and drafts back

100
00:06:12,950 --> 00:06:15,600
for further examination?

101
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:16,760
Mr. Meng said

102
00:06:17,133 --> 00:06:19,422
every review must be approved by him.

103
00:06:21,830 --> 00:06:22,670
No worries.

104
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:25,311
Every single grain
and every inch of silk

105
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:26,160
is the people's

106
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:27,870
hard work.

107
00:06:28,270 --> 00:06:30,950
I'll investigate thoroughly

108
00:06:30,955 --> 00:06:32,511
and get to the bottom of it.

109
00:06:32,870 --> 00:06:33,710
Yes, Sir.

110
00:06:34,630 --> 00:06:35,480
Li Shande.

111
00:06:35,511 --> 00:06:37,800
(Bureau of Agriculture)
This fellow can discover corruption

112
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:38,844
but can't resolve it.

113
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:41,430
So, I'm assigning him

114
00:06:41,888 --> 00:06:43,466
to you for some training.

115
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:47,160
You're far-sighted, Sir.

116
00:06:47,750 --> 00:06:49,270
I'm impressed.

117
00:06:56,870 --> 00:06:58,155
What a devious fox.

118
00:07:12,390 --> 00:07:13,360
As expected,

119
00:07:13,511 --> 00:07:15,349
Li Shande got promoted
in just three days.

120
00:07:15,350 --> 00:07:16,950
He's transferred to the Shanglin Office.

121
00:07:16,950 --> 00:07:17,790
However,

122
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:19,870
Mr. Meng was found
tampering with the records

123
00:07:19,911 --> 00:07:21,422
and was disgraced in his final years.

124
00:07:21,466 --> 00:07:22,720
He was exiled

125
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:24,190
to a provincial granary.

126
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:26,200
That's all?

127
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:31,222
The record altered by Mr. Meng

128
00:07:31,355 --> 00:07:33,950
was actually reviewed
by the Vice Minister.

129
00:07:35,750 --> 00:07:36,680
Li Shande

130
00:07:36,822 --> 00:07:38,377
is such a fool.

131
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:40,800
He insisted on exposing this

132
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:43,511
and ended up offending
the Vice Minister.

133
00:07:44,622 --> 00:07:47,111
My brother
at the Ministry of Personnel told me

134
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:49,555
that he'd only been there for three days

135
00:07:49,777 --> 00:07:51,377
and already got Mr. Meng expelled

136
00:07:51,377 --> 00:07:52,622
from the Bureau of Agriculture.

137
00:07:52,630 --> 00:07:53,470
What?

138
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:56,270
Chief Liu

139
00:07:56,270 --> 00:07:57,480
offended him last time

140
00:07:58,600 --> 00:08:00,266
and mocked him with carp.

141
00:08:03,630 --> 00:08:04,830
If Li Shande

142
00:08:04,830 --> 00:08:06,040
reports him

143
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:08,688
for eating peaches
from the imperial garden

144
00:08:08,750 --> 00:08:09,800
without permission,

145
00:08:10,870 --> 00:08:13,070
wouldn't he end up

146
00:08:13,630 --> 00:08:14,800
like Mr. Meng,

147
00:08:15,022 --> 00:08:16,466
exiled to some remote province?

148
00:08:25,830 --> 00:08:26,830
Chief Liu.

149
00:08:28,160 --> 00:08:28,710
Chief Liu.

150
00:08:28,830 --> 00:08:29,670
Chief Liu.

151
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:35,920
Liangyuan,

152
00:08:36,022 --> 00:08:38,000
there's something
I need to discuss with you.

153
00:08:40,080 --> 00:08:41,790
I believe you're a man of talent.

154
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:43,550
I wish you could prove yourself.

155
00:08:45,360 --> 00:08:47,120
Since you have some knowledge

156
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:48,720
about flowers, birds, fish, and insects,

157
00:08:48,733 --> 00:08:51,270
why don't you take up duty
at Leyou Garden?

158
00:08:55,910 --> 00:08:56,480
Sir,

159
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:58,000
I'm from the arithmetic division.

160
00:09:00,390 --> 00:09:01,360
Sir, flowers...

161
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:05,920
Supervisor Li.

162
00:09:35,500 --> 00:09:38,500
=Episode 25=

163
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:41,360
This pink silk-embroidered circular fan

164
00:09:42,030 --> 00:09:43,630
clearly belongs to a lady.

165
00:09:44,022 --> 00:09:45,733
Could it be there's a woman here

166
00:09:45,800 --> 00:09:47,790
who has caught your eye, Guiyun?

167
00:09:49,030 --> 00:09:51,320
This is my fan.

168
00:09:51,790 --> 00:09:52,630
You must be kidding.

169
00:09:53,750 --> 00:09:54,480
Look.

170
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:56,630
There's a hidden design.

171
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:00,666
It makes me look fairer.

172
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:03,870
The two characters here say "Longing".

173
00:10:03,870 --> 00:10:04,977
How do you explain this?

174
00:10:05,540 --> 00:10:07,180
(Longing)

175
00:10:08,910 --> 00:10:11,030
To others, it means longing for lovers.

176
00:10:12,390 --> 00:10:14,240
But to me,

177
00:10:14,955 --> 00:10:16,733
(Longing for Chancellor)
it's read differently.

178
00:10:18,670 --> 00:10:19,510
Longing for Chancellor?

179
00:10:23,910 --> 00:10:26,360
No news heard from the one I care for
who is far away.

180
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:29,670
Though we are far apart,
we share the same moon.

181
00:10:30,750 --> 00:10:32,030
I may be in Lingnan,

182
00:10:32,311 --> 00:10:34,244
but I think of the Right Chancellor
every day.

183
00:10:34,466 --> 00:10:36,311
Every time I drink alone
under the moonlight

184
00:10:36,444 --> 00:10:38,066
and look north where Chang'an stands,

185
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:40,790
thoughts well up in my heart.

186
00:10:40,960 --> 00:10:42,600
I can't hold back my tears.

187
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:45,630
Hence, I wrote this

188
00:10:45,960 --> 00:10:47,670
to ease my pain of longing.

189
00:10:48,510 --> 00:10:49,600
The Right Chancellor

190
00:10:49,840 --> 00:10:51,870
will surely be moved by your sincerity.

191
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:53,800
I hope so.

192
00:10:54,270 --> 00:10:55,550
Perhaps this bookstore

193
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:57,840
holds only the books you need,

194
00:10:57,840 --> 00:11:00,030
but never the ones I need.

195
00:11:03,270 --> 00:11:05,600
If that is so, I take my leave.

196
00:11:05,870 --> 00:11:06,720
Take care, Xinmin.

197
00:11:06,840 --> 00:11:07,680
Farewell.

198
00:11:31,022 --> 00:11:32,160
Attendant Yu,

199
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:33,080
it's dark.

200
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:34,040
Watch your footing.

201
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:36,844
Save your flattery.

202
00:11:37,333 --> 00:11:40,155
Serving Noble Consort is what matters.

203
00:11:40,822 --> 00:11:42,270
Right Chancellor warns

204
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:44,150
that this birthday banquet

205
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:45,733
must be done properly.

206
00:11:46,390 --> 00:11:47,910
There's not much time left.

207
00:11:48,750 --> 00:11:50,910
How are the tributes from every region
coming along?

208
00:11:51,750 --> 00:11:52,870
All birthday tributes

209
00:11:52,870 --> 00:11:53,750
are on the way.

210
00:11:54,111 --> 00:11:56,088
Gifts from foreign states
have crossed the borders

211
00:11:56,133 --> 00:11:58,266
and should arrive in Chang'an
by next month.

212
00:11:59,320 --> 00:12:00,160
When they arrive,

213
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:02,244
assign more men to
the Imperial Household Department

214
00:12:02,244 --> 00:12:03,822
and Left Storage Office to keep watch.

215
00:12:04,150 --> 00:12:05,577
Make sure nothing goes wrong.

216
00:12:06,044 --> 00:12:07,480
Aside from the birthday tributes,

217
00:12:07,822 --> 00:12:09,466
the local specialties from each region

218
00:12:09,510 --> 00:12:10,733
must also arrive on time.

219
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:13,488
You need to keep a close watch
from time to time.

220
00:12:13,750 --> 00:12:14,590
Yes, Sir.

221
00:12:15,670 --> 00:12:16,510
Attendant Yu,

222
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:17,840
speaking of which,

223
00:12:17,955 --> 00:12:19,888
there's been quite some news lately.

224
00:12:20,360 --> 00:12:22,822
That Litchi Envoy
has returned from Lingnan.

225
00:12:23,480 --> 00:12:24,320
Litchi Envoy?

226
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:25,750
Have you forgotten?

227
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:27,622
You saw him at the Leyou Garden.

228
00:12:27,960 --> 00:12:29,244
When he was first appointed,

229
00:12:29,270 --> 00:12:30,110
he panicked,

230
00:12:30,630 --> 00:12:32,000
saying that transporting litchis

231
00:12:32,030 --> 00:12:33,866
from Lingnan to Chang'an was impossible.

232
00:12:34,080 --> 00:12:35,960
You told him
he might as well wait to die.

233
00:12:36,790 --> 00:12:37,750
That fool

234
00:12:38,120 --> 00:12:39,270
now claims he's found a way

235
00:12:39,270 --> 00:12:40,866
to transport fresh litchis.

236
00:12:41,080 --> 00:12:42,320
He's been to every office

237
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:43,266
to submit his petition,

238
00:12:43,270 --> 00:12:45,120
but he was shut out and kicked around

239
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:46,150
like a ball.

240
00:12:50,150 --> 00:12:52,600
He even dared to go

241
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:54,155
to the Ministry of War.

242
00:12:54,790 --> 00:12:55,630
He got thrown out

243
00:12:55,870 --> 00:12:57,400
and nearly scared to death.

244
00:12:59,390 --> 00:13:02,000
Desperately fighting
even when he's cornered

245
00:13:02,030 --> 00:13:03,630
for a chance.

246
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:07,270
This Litchi Envoy

247
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:10,555
reminds me of my past.

248
00:13:11,270 --> 00:13:12,110
Attendant Yu,

249
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:14,377
it was an amazing act
that you transported wax

250
00:13:14,440 --> 00:13:15,390
by horses.

251
00:13:15,444 --> 00:13:16,777
No one can replicate that.

252
00:13:16,960 --> 00:13:18,790
How could that Litchi Envoy

253
00:13:19,240 --> 00:13:20,390
compare to you?

254
00:13:22,133 --> 00:13:24,044
Great rewards lie in great risk.

255
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:26,390
Opportunities often come

256
00:13:27,320 --> 00:13:29,844
from great danger.

257
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:32,333
If that Litchi Envoy

258
00:13:32,630 --> 00:13:34,120
has found a method

259
00:13:34,120 --> 00:13:36,000
to transport fresh litchis,

260
00:13:37,510 --> 00:13:38,480
that means

261
00:13:40,030 --> 00:13:40,910
he's holding a chance

262
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:43,390
that could lead to boundless fortune.

263
00:13:45,870 --> 00:13:46,710
Speak up.

264
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:51,400
How did the peony get infested?

265
00:13:51,533 --> 00:13:52,933
How many days has it been?

266
00:13:53,720 --> 00:13:54,560
Two days.

267
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:56,560
Two days?

268
00:13:56,911 --> 00:13:58,960
And you didn't say a word.

269
00:13:59,750 --> 00:14:00,866
Why didn't you tell me?

270
00:14:01,240 --> 00:14:02,150
What's wrong with you?

271
00:14:04,550 --> 00:14:07,711
You haven't come by for two days.

272
00:14:08,360 --> 00:14:09,390
We couldn't possibly

273
00:14:09,390 --> 00:14:10,870
go to the Shanglin Office on our own.

274
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:12,040
This is bad.

275
00:14:14,022 --> 00:14:15,466
The Right Chancellor is coming

276
00:14:15,910 --> 00:14:17,550
this afternoon.

277
00:14:18,750 --> 00:14:21,000
If he sees this,

278
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:24,022
we'll all be punished.

279
00:14:27,080 --> 00:14:27,920
Catch the bugs.

280
00:14:28,510 --> 00:14:30,670
Get everyone to catch the bugs.

281
00:14:31,550 --> 00:14:32,360
But

282
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:34,044
we can't catch them all.

283
00:14:34,120 --> 00:14:35,270
It needs pesticides.

284
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:36,977
You think I need you to tell me that?

285
00:14:38,150 --> 00:14:40,866
If you can't come up
with a proper formula

286
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:43,200
and end up killing the peony,

287
00:14:43,670 --> 00:14:45,480
we'll all lose our heads.

288
00:14:46,270 --> 00:14:48,550
That's His Majesty's favorite peony.

289
00:14:49,240 --> 00:14:50,755
How could you be so careless?

290
00:14:51,480 --> 00:14:53,200
You can't blame me for that.

291
00:14:54,840 --> 00:14:56,400
After Li Shande left,

292
00:14:57,390 --> 00:14:59,044
we agreed

293
00:14:59,320 --> 00:15:02,177
we'd all take care
of the peony together.

294
00:15:03,480 --> 00:15:04,320
Well,

295
00:15:05,120 --> 00:15:06,790
it's the leaves that got infested.

296
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:09,480
How is that on me?

297
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:13,755
How could you say that?

298
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,480
I'm in charge of pruning the branches,

299
00:15:18,270 --> 00:15:20,870
and I trim only dry ones

300
00:15:20,870 --> 00:15:22,270
with extreme care.

301
00:15:23,066 --> 00:15:26,000
I've done it more carefully
than I cut my mother's nails.

302
00:15:26,320 --> 00:15:27,720
The bugs must've come

303
00:15:30,240 --> 00:15:31,270
from the soil.

304
00:15:34,030 --> 00:15:34,870
I loosen the soil

305
00:15:35,030 --> 00:15:36,720
and fertilize it,

306
00:15:36,911 --> 00:15:37,839
but I use only

307
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:39,150
the finest rake

308
00:15:39,150 --> 00:15:40,000
and fertilizer.

309
00:15:40,240 --> 00:15:41,080
If it's

310
00:15:41,080 --> 00:15:42,440
the soil and the fertilizer,

311
00:15:42,670 --> 00:15:44,360
shouldn't we ask

312
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:46,400
the procurement clerk and treasurer?

313
00:15:48,977 --> 00:15:50,150
If I had bought fertilizer

314
00:15:50,150 --> 00:15:51,440
with insect eggs in it,

315
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:52,550
why did the bugs

316
00:15:52,550 --> 00:15:53,440
only appear now?

317
00:15:54,440 --> 00:15:56,240
I think

318
00:15:56,630 --> 00:15:58,044
someone must've slacked off.

319
00:15:59,150 --> 00:16:00,670
It must be the fault

320
00:16:00,670 --> 00:16:02,511
of the protective mesh.

321
00:16:02,630 --> 00:16:04,200
It allowed the bugs in.

322
00:16:06,630 --> 00:16:09,200
Yes, I'm in charge
of the protective mesh.

323
00:16:09,790 --> 00:16:11,390
But my brother,

324
00:16:11,422 --> 00:16:13,222
who is director
of the Ministry of Personnel,

325
00:16:13,288 --> 00:16:14,630
always teaches me

326
00:16:15,270 --> 00:16:18,266
that you can never tell with people.

327
00:16:19,750 --> 00:16:20,590
Sir,

328
00:16:20,733 --> 00:16:21,870
was the protection mesh

329
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:24,444
meant to block bugs?

330
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:26,720
This is indeed

331
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:28,509
a wrong accusation.

332
00:16:28,510 --> 00:16:31,270
Please judge fairly, Sir.

333
00:16:34,630 --> 00:16:35,510
In that case,

334
00:16:36,270 --> 00:16:37,822
none of you is to blame.

335
00:16:42,066 --> 00:16:45,066
I'm in charge of all the gardens
under the Shanglin Office.

336
00:16:45,355 --> 00:16:47,200
If I have to inspect everything myself,

337
00:16:47,390 --> 00:16:48,870
a peony today,

338
00:16:49,320 --> 00:16:50,720
a bamboo tomorrow,

339
00:16:50,720 --> 00:16:52,000
or every single trivial task,

340
00:16:52,480 --> 00:16:54,088
what do I need you all for?

341
00:16:55,960 --> 00:16:56,800
This matter

342
00:16:57,222 --> 00:16:58,688
must be made clear today.

343
00:16:58,720 --> 00:17:00,244
Someone has to take the responsibility.

344
00:17:06,720 --> 00:17:09,600
I heard Li Shande is back.

345
00:17:11,270 --> 00:17:12,110
Really?

346
00:17:12,440 --> 00:17:13,280
Yes.

347
00:17:14,750 --> 00:17:15,720
It's said

348
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:18,070
that he caused quite a scene

349
00:17:18,510 --> 00:17:19,720
at every office

350
00:17:20,350 --> 00:17:22,111
with his litchi petition.

351
00:17:22,680 --> 00:17:23,920
He didn't get the permit

352
00:17:24,310 --> 00:17:25,240
and got shut out.

353
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:28,840
Sir,

354
00:17:29,240 --> 00:17:30,200
in fact,

355
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:32,888
Li Shande was the one taking care
of this peony in the first place.

356
00:17:32,920 --> 00:17:34,640
We're only helping out

357
00:17:34,960 --> 00:17:36,310
as colleagues.

358
00:17:37,030 --> 00:17:37,870
Exactly.

359
00:17:38,240 --> 00:17:39,590
Who knows if the peony got infested

360
00:17:39,590 --> 00:17:42,310
because he patched the broken branch

361
00:17:42,440 --> 00:17:44,200
with yellow mud?

362
00:17:44,640 --> 00:17:45,960
The peony was wounded,

363
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:48,030
and the dirty mud

364
00:17:48,550 --> 00:17:50,790
got into its core

365
00:17:51,270 --> 00:17:53,070
while it was weak.

366
00:17:53,350 --> 00:17:54,400
Of course,

367
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:56,110
it'd get infested over time.

368
00:17:56,550 --> 00:17:57,280
In that case,

369
00:17:57,400 --> 00:17:59,222
Li Shande should take the blame.

370
00:18:01,680 --> 00:18:02,520
Him?

371
00:18:02,960 --> 00:18:04,440
He'll soon face his demise.

372
00:18:04,440 --> 00:18:05,790
He has nothing left to lose.

373
00:18:06,510 --> 00:18:08,444
Why would he take the blame?

374
00:18:13,270 --> 00:18:17,844
We could trick him into
coming back to Leyou Garden.

375
00:18:18,590 --> 00:18:20,755
Who else could still fool him now?

376
00:18:21,960 --> 00:18:23,350
If not,

377
00:18:24,444 --> 00:18:26,466
we'll try something else.

378
00:18:33,310 --> 00:18:36,444
Sir, please help me.

379
00:18:38,270 --> 00:18:40,350
I have an eighty-year-old mother,

380
00:18:40,480 --> 00:18:42,866
(Shanglin Office)
sir!

381
00:18:44,510 --> 00:18:47,955
Even though Li Shande
is now the Litchi Envoy,

382
00:18:48,030 --> 00:18:50,790
he was once our colleague.

383
00:18:51,711 --> 00:18:53,149
Now he's returned to Chang'an

384
00:18:53,150 --> 00:18:54,880
and is being turned away
by every office...

385
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:01,840
Why don't we

386
00:19:02,590 --> 00:19:03,430
invite him over

387
00:19:04,750 --> 00:19:07,200
for a catch-up?

388
00:19:09,240 --> 00:19:10,310
- Yes, Sir.
